    • isGenerateJacksonAnnotations

      boolean isGenerateJacksonAnnotations()

      The Jackson annotations are necessary to properly deserialize the json, that is incoming from the GraphQL Server. Setting this property to false allows to not generate them.

      If this property is set to true, the Jackson annotations are added in the generated GraphQL objects. The Jackson dependencies must then be added to the target project, so that the project compiles.

      The default value is:

      • true when in client mode.
      • false when in server mode.
      Specified by:
      isGenerateJacksonAnnotations in interface CommonConfiguration
      Specified by:
      isGenerateJacksonAnnotations in interface GenerateClientCodeConfiguration
      Specified by:
      isGenerateJacksonAnnotations in interface GenerateServerCodeConfiguration
      Specified by:
      isGenerateJacksonAnnotations in interface GraphQLConfiguration
      Returns:
      The GeneratePojoConfiguration implementation of this method always returns true
